name: Redlands East Valley High School: Theatre/Music Building
comment: You can only is it if you have permission to borrow the keys from a music teacher or the theatre teacher, but it's the only gender neutral restroom I've seen in the whole high school. It's one stall and you have to put your name date and time on a sign in sheet, but it's really nice. It has a toilet, a tampon trashcan, a sink, a mirror, a toilet paper roll holder (normally very we'll stocked), and a blow dryer for your hands. It doesn't lock from the inside with a bolt though and you need to always knock before entering. It's kind of spacious too, but I don't remember if there's a bar there to help yourself up or down.
